{"title": "How to Paint Permanent Pictures", "description": "\"How To Paint Permanent Pictures\" by Maximilian Toch delves into the intricate art of creating lasting images through painting. Toch, a passionate expert in the field, explains the techniques and materials essential for achieving long lasting artwork. He explores the chemistry behind pigments, binders, and varnishes, offering insights into their properties and interactions. Through meticulous detail and practical advice, Toch guides aspiring artists and professionals alike in navigating the complexities of preserving their creations for posterity. By understanding the science behind pigmentation and surface treatment, painters can ensure the longevity and durability of their works. Toch's treatise not only serves as a valuable resource for artists but also underscores the intersection of art and science. \"How to Paint Permanent Pictures\" finds the beauty inherent in the science of painting, his gamut of colors, from Alizarin Green to Zinnober Red,  burst out of the page and make this short 12000 word work, a kaleidoscope through which to view and understand paint selection. - Summary by Bryn Roberts", "duration": 5674, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "18237", "name": "Maximilian Toch"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/howtopaintpermanentpictures_2403_librivox/paintpermanent_2303.jpg", "copyright_year": "1922", "genres": ["Art", "Design & Architecture"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Bryn Roberts"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Bryn Roberts"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "redrun"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Laura Victoria"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface", "readers": [18007], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/howtopaintpermanentpictures_2403_librivox/htppp_00_toch_64kb.mp3", "duration": 126}, {"section": 1, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [18007], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/howtopaintpermanentpictu